# Docker build context = repo ROOT for both images:
#   docker build -f apps/web/Dockerfile        -t lumen-web    .
#   docker build -f apps/web/worker/Dockerfile -t lumen-worker .
# Docker reads .dockerignore from the context root, so this one file trims the
# context for both Railway builds. Keep it small, and never ship local deps or
# secrets into the image (both Dockerfiles reinstall via `bun install`).

# Dependencies — reinstalled with `bun install --frozen-lockfile`
**/node_modules

# Build outputs + caches
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
.git
.github

# Local env + secrets — never bake into an image
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Tests + reports — not needed at runtime
**/*.test.ts
**/__tests__
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# Agent + editor + OS cruft
.claude
.agents
**/.DS_Store
